  "prompt": "How does evolution work for humans?",
  "response": "Evolution for humans works through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. Natural Selection\n- Organisms with beneficial traits are more likely to survive and reproduce\n- Traits that improve survival and reproduction get passed to offspring\n- Advantageous genetic variations become more common over generations\n\n2. Genetic Variation\n- Occurs through mutations in DNA\n- Sexual reproduction creates genetic diversity by mixing parental genes\n- Different gene combinations produce unique traits\n\n3. Inheritance\n- Genetic traits are passed from parents to children\n- Some traits are dominant, some recessive\n- Genetic inheritance determines physical and biological characteristics\n\n4. Adaptation\n- Populations gradually change in response to environmental pressures\n- Traits that help survival in specific environments become more prevalent\n- Examples include resistance to diseases or ability to live in certain climates\n\n5. Population Genetics\n- Changes occur at the population level over many generations\n- Small genetic shifts accumulate over time\n- Large populations have more genetic diversity\n\n6. Sexual Selection\n- Traits that attract mates become more common\n- Certain characteristics are perceived as more desirable\n- Influences physical and behavioral traits\n\nThese processes have shaped human development over hundreds of thousands of years, leading to our current biological characteristics and diversity.",
